Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C.

Zest and halve the @lime{½}.

Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces.

Trim the @spring onion{2} then slice thinly.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #sieve{} and pop into a #bowl{}. Crush the beans with
the back of a #fork{} until slightly broken up.

Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{150} in a sieve.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Chicken Mixture ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} (preferably non-stick) over medium-high
heat.

Once hot, add the @vivera plant chicken pieces{175} and stir fry until golden brown all
over, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Transfer to a #plate{}, but don't wash up the pan!

Return the pan to the heat with a drizzle more oil if needed. Add the shallot and cook,
stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the garlic and @Mexican spice and continue to cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @water for the sauce{100%ml} and @vegetable stock powder{1}, stir to dissolve the
stock.

Add the black beans, sweetcorn and chicken pieces, season with @salt{} and @ground black
pepper{} and stir together.

Bring to a simmer and cook until the liquid has reduced and the sauce has thickened,
~{6-8%minutes}.

== Lime Mayonnaise ==

Pop the @mayonnaise{1}, lime zest and a squeeze of lime juice into a small bowl.

Season with salt and pepper and stir together. Add a splash of water and stir until it
has a pourable consistency.

Cut any remaining lime into wedges.

== Tostadas ==

A few minutes before the chicken mixture is ready, lay the @plain taco tortillas{6} on
a large #baking tray{} in a single layer and drizzle with a little @oil{}.

Season with salt and bake on the top shelf of the oven until golden and crispy,
~{4-5%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

When everything is ready, divide the tacos between plates and top with the chicken and
bean mixture.

Drizzle over the lime mayo, scatter over the spring onion and serve with lime wedges
alongside. Enjoy!